getSubPart

public INeuronMorphologyPart getSubPart(int x)
Retrieves the segment at number i. IMPORTANT NOTE: This method does not return a new reference each time it is called. Instead it uses the same instance of a segment each time and simply calls a set method to make it into the appropriate segment. Do not add these segments to any collections or they will not work correctly. This is in an effort to save memory due to the large number of ISegments that the system needs to deal with

Specified by:
getSubPart in interface INeuronMorphologyPart
Returns:
the sub part. null if it is not found.
